The paper deals with visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of correlation filters and the focus on learning how both foreground and background vary over time suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new approach that involves learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve tracking benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
